From David Nye Subject Re Faith and Dogma reply to Todd Kelley In light of what happened in Waco I need to get something of my Faith and dogma are A philosopher cannot be a Christian because a philosopher can change his mind whereas a Christian cannot due to the nature of faith and dogma present in any It is hard for me to understand but quite a few professional scientists and philosophers are Sure religion has many good It encourages benevolence and But also intolerance and I'm not sure that in the balance it is not Wouldn't it be nice if everyone were a secular humanist Sure would David Nye Midelfort Clinic Eau Claire WI This is patently absurd but whoever wishes to become a philosopher must learn not to be frightened by Bertrand Russell